  "prompt": "What are some greatest operations by Ajit Doval?",
  "response": "Ajit Doval, a former Indian Police Service (IPS) officer and the current National Security Advisor of India, is renowned for his strategic acumen and several significant operations. Here are some of his most notable operations:\n\n1. **Operation Black Thunder II (1988)**:\n   - Doval played a crucial role in the planning and execution of Operation Black Thunder II, aimed at flushing out militants from the Golden Temple in Amritsar. His undercover work and negotiations were pivotal in the success of this operation, which was completed with minimal collateral damage.\n\n2. **Infiltration in Pakistan (1990s)**:\n   - Doval spent seven years in Pakistan undercover, gathering intelligence and building networks. He posed as a Muslim and worked as a teacher and a journalist, among other roles. This operation significantly enhanced India's intelligence capabilities regarding Pakistan.\n\n3. **Kandahar Hijacking (1999)**:\n   - During the hijacking of Indian Airlines flight IC-814, Doval was part of the crisis management team. Although the operation ended with the release of three terrorists in exchange for the hostages, Doval's role in managing the negotiations was crucial.\n\n4. **Operation against Laskhar-e-Taiba (2002)**:\n   - Doval was instrumental in the successful infiltration of the Lashkar-e-Taiba (LeT) network, leading to the arrest of key operatives and the dismantling of several modules within India.\n\n5. **Surgical Strikes (2016)**:\n   - As the National Security Advisor, Doval was the chief architect of the surgical strikes conducted by the Indian Army against terrorist launch pads across the Line of Control in response to the Uri attack. The operation was a significant demonstration of India's resolve and capability.\n\n6. **Balakot Air Strike (2019)**:\n   - Doval played a pivotal role in the planning and execution of the Balakot airstrike, targeting a Jaish-e-Mohammed terrorist training camp in Pakistan following the Pulwama attack. This was a landmark operation in showcasing India's readiness to strike terror targets across borders.\n\n7. **Hostage Rescue in Yemen (2015)**:\n   - Doval was instrumental in the evacuation of Indian nationals from Yemen during the civil war. His strategic planning and coordination with various agencies ensured the safe return of over 4,000 Indian citizens in a highly volatile situation.\n\n8. **Doklam Standoff (2017)**:\n   - Doval's diplomatic efforts and strategic handling were crucial during the Doklam standoff between India and China. His negotiations helped in de-escalating the situation and reaching a peaceful resolution.\n\nThese operations highlight Ajit Doval's extensive experience in intelligence, counter-terrorism, and strategic affairs, showcasing his significant contributions to India's national security.",
